#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi.rst:5
msgid "Kexec Handover ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi.rst:8
msgid "Core Kexec Handover ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:21
msgid ""
"Kexec Handover uses the ABI defined below for passing preserved data from "
"one kernel to the next. The ABI uses Flattened Device Tree (FDT) format. The "
"first kernel creates an FDT which is then passed to the next kernel during a "
"kexec handover."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:26
msgid ""
"This interface is a contract. Any modification to the FDT structure, node "
"properties, compatible string, or the layout of the data structures "
"referenced here constitutes a breaking change. Such changes require "
"incrementing the version number in KHO_FDT_COMPATIBLE to prevent a new "
"kernel from misinterpreting data from an older kernel. Changes are allowed "
"provided the compatibility version is incremented. However, backward/forward "
"compatibility is only guaranteed for kernels supporting the same ABI version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:34
#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:22: ../include/linux/kho/abi/memblock.h:22
msgid "FDT Structure Overview:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:35
msgid ""
"The FDT serves as a central registry for physical addresses of preserved "
"data structures. The first kernel populates this FDT with references to "
"memory regions and other metadata that need to persist across the kexec "
"transition. The subsequent kernel then parses this FDT to locate and restore "
"the preserved data.::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:62
msgid "Root KHO Node (/):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:63
msgid "compatible: \"kho-v3\""
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:65
msgid "Indentifies the overall KHO ABI version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:67
msgid "preserved-memory-map: u64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:69
msgid ""
"Physical memory address pointing to the root of the preserved memory map "
"data structure."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:72
msgid "Subnodes (<subnode-name-N>):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:73
msgid ""
"Subnodes can also be added to the root node to describe other preserved data "
"blobs. The <subnode-name-N> is provided by the subsystem that uses KHO for "
"preserving its data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:78
msgid "preserved-data: u64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:80
msgid ""
"Physical address pointing to a subnode data blob that is also being "
"preserved."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:83
msgid "blob-size: u64"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:10: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:85
msgid ""
"Size in bytes of the preserved data blob. This is needed because blobs may "
"use arbitrary formats (not just FDT), so the size cannot be determined from "
"the blob content alone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi.rst:14
msgid "vmalloc preservation ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:16: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:105
msgid ""
"The Kexec Handover ABI for preserving vmalloc'ed memory is defined by a set "
"of structures and helper macros. The layout of these structures is a stable "
"contract between kernels and is versioned by the KHO_FDT_COMPATIBLE string."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:16: ../include/linux/kho/abi/kexec_handover.h:110
msgid ""
"The preservation is managed through a main descriptor :c:type:`struct "
"kho_vmalloc <kho_vmalloc>`, which points to a linked list of :c:type:`struct "
"kho_vmalloc_chunk <kho_vmalloc_chunk>` structures. These chunks contain the "
"physical addresses of the preserved pages, allowing the next kernel to "
"reconstruct the vmalloc area with the same content and layout. Helper macros "
"are also defined for storing and loading pointers within these structures."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi.rst:20
msgid "memblock preservation ABI"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:22: ../include/linux/kho/abi/memblock.h:7
msgid ""
"Memblock can serialize its current memory reservations created with "
"reserve_mem command line option across kexec through KHO. The post-KHO "
"kernel can then consume these reservations and they are guaranteed to have "
"the same physical address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:22: ../include/linux/kho/abi/memblock.h:12
msgid ""
"The state is serialized using Flattened Device Tree (FDT) format. Any "
"modification to the FDT structure, node properties, or the compatible "
"strings constitutes a breaking change. Such changes require incrementing the "
"version number in the relevant `_COMPATIBLE` string to prevent a new kernel "
"from misinterpreting data from an old kernel."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:22: ../include/linux/kho/abi/memblock.h:18
msgid ""
"Changes are allowed provided the compatibility version is incremented. "
"However, backward/forward compatibility is only guaranteed for kernels "
"supporting the same ABI version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../core-api/kho/abi:22: ../include/linux/kho/abi/memblock.h:23
msgid ""
"The entire memblock state is encapsulated within a single KHO entry named "
"\"memblock\". This entry contains an FDT with the following layout:"
msgstr ""

